{"key":"processedPost-8089288","value":{"id":8089288,"first":8083509,"last":8093602,"when":1204393426,"utime":"03/01/08 07:43 PM","content":"Use half as much water/coffee by volume as rye grass seed.  In other words, for 1/2 cup of rye grass seed, use 1/4 cup of coffee/water.  For a quart mason jar, use 1 1/4 cup of rye grass seed and 5/8 cup water.  I still stand by my statement that rye berries will give more sclerotia faster, but suit yourself.  The rye grass seed teks are outdated and obsolete.<br />RR","title":"Re: Growing philosopher stones question","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}